arcane - qmk keyboard configuration
===================================
arcane is a flashy mechanical keyboard configuration with some special lighting
functionality. arcane lights up reactively when a key is pressed and operates
independently on both sides of a split keyboard.

Installation
------------
Install qmk firmware and teensy_loader_cli:

    $ git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/zsa/qmk_firmware/
    # pacman -S teensy_loader_cli

Downgrade avr-gcc to version 8.3.0:

    # pacman -U https://archive.archlinux.org/packages/a/avr-gcc/avr-gcc-8.3.0-1-x86_64.pkg.tar.xz

Install udev rules:

    # cp qmk_firmware/util/udev/50-qmk.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/

Clone arcane and move it to the proper location:

    $ git clone https://github.com/arcnyxx/arcane/
    $ mv arcane qmk_firmware/keyboards/ergodox_ez/glow/keymaps

Build and flash arcane:

    $ cd qmk_firmware; make -j 1 ergodox_ez/glow:arcane:flash

